children.text: The brickwork panel in this area has no ties in it to properly support the brick-veneer wall.
Part 3.3.5.10 Wall ties of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘Veneer wall ties must be spaced and fixed in accordance with Table 3.3.5.3a’ .
Additionally, Australian Standard, AS 3700 - Masonry Structures requires in section 4.10 Wall Ties that
‘Wall ties for cavity and masonry veneer walls shall be spaced no greater than 600mm in each direction’ .
As there are no brick ties in this area, and Australian Standard AS 3700 states that
‘Wall ties and accessories embedded in mortar joints shall be built in as the construction proceeds’

, this section of brickwork will need to be demolished and reconstructed with brick ties connecting to the timber frame in accordance with the requirements of the Building Code of Australia (BCA) and relevant standards.
